descript.abstract: The Relationship Detail Static Metadata table records the pairs of join columns that define a particular relationship. Each record in this table represents one pair of join columns for a particular relationship.

idinfo.native: Microsoft Windows 7 Version 6.1 (Build 7601) Service Pack 1; Esri ArcGIS 10.1.1.3143

attr.attrdef: The physical name of a column of a table on the right side of a relationship between two tables. This column is one of several potential columns used to create a join between the two tables involved in a relationship. The right table column joins to its corresponding left table column.
A name given to a relationship between two tables. If there is more than one relationship between the same two tables, the name of each of those relationships must be unique.

The physical name of a column of a table on the left side of a relationship between two tables. This column is one of several potential columns used to create a join between the two tables involved in a relationship. The left table column joins to its corresponding right table column.
The physical name of a table on the right side of a relationship between two tables.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: The physical name of a table on the left side of a relationship between two tables.
